Jealousy is the biggest red flag anyone can run up a mast!<br>
People are most often jealous because they feel inferior..some folks feel inferior because they are inferior!  Why are they inferior..because they have always lacked internalized values.. the foundation of self esteem. A lot of folks have learned dysfunctions.. not something that was handed to them by the War experience but by a lack of nurturing in childhood.  I'm the first to expound upon the horrors of PTSD secondary to combat, also first to ferret out manipulative con-men and predators.  I hope your &quot;friend&quot; is neither.  If he is fooling around on you (I hope he's not!) then he is trying to shore up his weak concept of manhood..needs daily reassurance that he has what it takes...usually from multiple sources.  Some guys often embellish there combat experiences to manipulate co-dependent women (hope you're not one)..or at least rescuers, idealist..etc.<br>
For your sake and the Boc's who love you...I hope he is a Good Guy and just needs some help.<br>
No man can tell another man what to do!  But, I strongly advise you to look with cognitive eyes instead of emotional eyes at your situation.  Look at what is there rather than look for what you want to be there.<br>
You might start by checking his DD 214.  Sorry, just don't trust folks.  If your dog don't have rabies..get'em a shot. If he does have rabies...don't pet him anymore!<br><br>
In the Special Forces..we said, &quot;Keep it simple, Stupid!&quot;<br>
Conduct of a courtship doesn't convey license to misrepresent to gain favor or control.  Jealousy = insecurity = need to control = manipulator.<br><br>
&quot;Say what you mean..Mean what you say..and don't Jack around, 'cause I ain't got all day!&quot;<br><br>
Good Luck Mom - MTF
